Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Roberta R Sanapaw

records.addlTxt: 1:26 PM Prosecuting attorney Alexander Paul Seifert in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Roberta R Sanapaw in court.  Attorney Breanna A. Halyburton in court for Roberta R Sanapaw. State calls Det. Sgt. Michael Short. Sworn in, 1:27 PM. State directs. State asks for stipulation of identification of defendant and if not, is asking for an adjournment to allow him to obtain a booking photo. Halyburton will not stipulate to identification. Court will allow adjournment for 30 minutes. Off record, 1:33 PM. Back on record, 1:48 PM. Witness is still under oath. State continues direct. Attorney Halyburton cross-examines witness, 1:50 PM.  Record reflects proper identification of defendant, 1:51 PM. Court finds probable cause and binds over for trial. Information has been filed. Attorney Halyburton will proceed to ARGN, waives further reading of information and enters not guilty pleas. Court accepts pleas, continues bond and will have set for JT.
Preliminary hearing on August 10, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

records.addlTxt:
11:01 AM Prosecuting attorney Charles James Simono in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Roberta R Sanapaw in court.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin in court.  Attorney Breanna A. Halyburton in court for Roberta R Sanapaw. Halyburton and Sanapaw have complaint, waives reading of it, requests PH but will waive time limits for that, would like to be heard on bond. Court considers time limits waived, will hear bond argument, will set for PH on 7/27/22 at 1:45 PM. Halyburton - bond - asks for signature bond for stated reasons. State - bond - has not had a chance to review the criminal history as was not prepared to argue bond, wants at least $250.00 cash. Halyburton makes additional argument for bond reduction. Court - bond - reduces bond to $1500.00 signature bond, no consumption of alcohol refund bond to poster.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 27, 2022 at 01:45 pm.

Court instructs to contact SPD today and reminds her of her right to court appointed. Court sets bond at $500.00 cash with no consumption of alcohol, sets for AIA on 6/29/22 at 11:00 AM.
